==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bushing
<hw>Bush"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See 4th <er>Bush</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The operation of fitting bushes, or linings, into holes
or places where wear is to be received, or friction diminished, as pivot
holes, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Mech.)</fld> <def>A bush or lining; -- sometimes
called a <altname>thimble</altname>. See 4th <er>Bush</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bushless</ent>⟦br⟧
